FBIS4-1498 "drafr083_cs94022" FBIS-AFR-94-083-S Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Violent Incidents Reported at Polling Stations Violent Incidents Reported at Polling Stations Grenade Found on Suspected MK Member MB2904100694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0927 GMT 29 Apr 94 MB2904100694 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] East London April 29 SAPA -- A suspected member of African National Congress military wing, Umkhonto we Sizwe [Spear of the Nation], has been arrested after being found carrying a hand grenade at a polling station in Duncan Village, reports SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news. East London police confirmed that six men claiming to be ANC election monitors had tried to gain access to a guarded building housing sealed ballot boxes. When they were confronted by the security forces, one of the men fled, dropping a machine pistol. The grenade was found on another man.
